      "en": {
        "name": "Cardiac output",
        "category": "Vital signs",
        "subcategory": "Haemodynamics",
        "shortDescription": "Cardiac output — the volume of blood the heart pumps per minute; measured by thermodilution, Fick, pulse-contour, Doppler/echo or imaging. Reported in L/min.",
        "longDescription": "## Definition & Clinical Context\n\nCardiac output is the volume of blood the heart pumps each minute (heart rate × stroke volume), the central measure of how well the circulation is delivering blood to the body. Measuring it produces a flow value reported in litres per minute (L/min) [1]. There is no single way to measure it: in the intensive care unit it is most often obtained by thermodilution through a pulmonary-artery catheter, by pulse-contour analysis of an arterial waveform (e.g., PiCCO, FloTrac), or by the Fick method; in the echocardiography and cardiology laboratory it is derived from Doppler/2D/3D echocardiography, cardiac MR, CT, angiography or nuclear imaging. Each method appears as a distinct concept so the measurement technique is preserved.\n\nThis concept set captures **cardiac output values** across all measurement methods and across the chamber/vessel where flow is assessed (left ventricle, right ventricle, aortic root, pulmonary artery). Closely related but separate parameters — cardiac index (cardiac output normalised to body surface area), stroke volume, and central venous pressure — are not part of this set.\n\n## Included Concepts\n\nThis concept set contains 45 standard concepts (43 LOINC + 2 SNOMED). Because most concepts are the same quantity (cardiac output) measured by a different technique, they are grouped below by **method** and by **anatomical site**; the many echocardiographic calculation variants are described collectively rather than enumerated. The default for an unqualified value is *4221102 / 82799009 — Cardiac output (SNOMED)* or, for a left-ventricular value, *3005555 / 8741-1 — Left ventricular Cardiac output (LOINC)*.\n\n### Generic cardiac output\n\n- *4221102 / 82799009 — Cardiac output (SNOMED)*: The generic cardiac output, no method or site specified. Default mapping target.\n- *3005555 / 8741-1 — Left ventricular Cardiac output (LOINC)*: Left-ventricular cardiac output with no method specified (the left ventricle is the default chamber, as it drives systemic flow).\n- *4326660 / 428628004 — Right ventricular cardiac output (SNOMED)*: Right-ventricular cardiac output, no method specified.\n\n### By clinical (ICU / cath-lab) method\n\nThese are the methods most relevant to critical care and invasive haemodynamics.\n\n- *3003487 / 8736-1 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Fick method (LOINC)* and *3966088 / 101150-1 — Right ventricular Cardiac output by Fick method (LOINC)*: Fick method (from oxygen consumption and arteriovenous oxygen difference).\n- *3002309 / 8737-9 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Indicator dilution (LOINC)* and *3965272 / 101151-9 — Right ventricular Cardiac output by Indicator dilution (LOINC)*: Indicator/thermodilution (the pulmonary-artery-catheter and transpulmonary methods used in the ICU).\n- *21492228 / 76519-8 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Continuous (LOINC)* and *21490694 / 61014-7 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Intermitent measure (LOINC)*: Continuous vs. intermittent cardiac-output monitoring (e.g., continuous-CO pulmonary-artery catheters vs. bolus thermodilution).\n\n### By Doppler / echocardiography\n\n- *3004582 / 8735-3 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by US.doppler (LOINC)*, *3013377 / 17992-9 — Aorta root Cardiac output by US.doppler (LOINC)*, *3016873 / 17994-5 — Pulmonary artery Cardiac output by US (LOINC)*: Doppler-ultrasound cardiac output at the LV, aortic root and pulmonary artery (the basis of non-invasive and oesophageal-Doppler CO).\n- *3015207 / 24526-6 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by US (LOINC)*, *21493295 / 81390-7 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by US 3D (LOINC)*, *3013457 / 8731-2 — Ventricular Cardiac output by 2D echo (LOINC)*, *3028413 / 20214-3 — Right ventricular Cardiac output by US 2D tricuspid valve (LOINC)*: General 2D/3D echo cardiac output.\n- **Echocardiographic calculation-method variants**: a large group of LOINC concepts records LV (and ventricular) cardiac output computed from 2D or M-mode echo by a specific geometric method — method of disks (Simpson), modified Simpson, Teichholz, Gibson, cube, bullet, single-/biplane area-length, single-/biplane ellipse, and apical 2-chamber (A2C) / 4-chamber (A4C) views. Examples: *3028063 / 20209-3 — Ventricular Cardiac output by US.2D+Calculated by modified Simpson method*, *3027576 / 20213-5 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by US+Calculated by Teichholz method*, *46234877 / 76571-9 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by US.2D+Calculated by Gibson method*, *3022693 / 20205-1 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by US.2D+Calculated by bullet method*. These all yield a cardiac-output value; they differ only in the geometric formula the echo machine uses. One variant — *3036561 / 20332-3 — Left ventricular Cardiac output/Heart rate 4 chamber by US 2D modified single-plane calculated* — is the per-beat value (cardiac output divided by heart rate, i.e., stroke volume) reported under this LOINC family.\n\n### By cross-sectional / nuclear imaging\n\n- *3002046 / 8738-7 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by MR (LOINC)*: Cardiac MR.\n- *3019520 / 8734-6 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Spiral CT (LOINC)*: CT.\n- *3019293 / 8733-8 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Angiography single plane (LOINC)* and *3022862 / 8732-0 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Angiography biplane (LOINC)*: Contrast angiography.\n- *3020967 / 8739-5 — Left ventricular Cardiac output by Nuclear blood pool (LOINC)*: Nuclear blood-pool imaging.\n\n## Excluded Concepts\n\nThis set is kept as a comprehensive list of cardiac-output measurements; no concepts are excluded from the source list. Related parameters that are **not** part of this set: cardiac index (cardiac output per body surface area), stroke volume, cardiac-output-to-body-surface-area ratios, and other derived haemodynamic indices — these are separate variables. The SNOMED \"Cardiac output\" concept has no measurement descendants, so the set is a curated list rather than a hierarchy anchor.\n\n## Mapping Notes\n\n- *Default concept*: When the source records a cardiac-output value with no method or chamber, map to Cardiac output (4221102 / 82799009, SNOMED), or Left ventricular Cardiac output (3005555 / 8741-1, LOINC) if a left-ventricular value is implied. Do not infer a measurement method that is not documented.\n- *ICU monitors*: A thermodilution or transpulmonary cardiac output (PA catheter, PiCCO) maps to Indicator dilution (3002309 / 8737-9, LOINC); a continuous-CO monitor maps to the Continuous concept (21492228 / 76519-8, LOINC); a pulse-contour value with no stated method maps to the generic concept.\n- *Echo calculation method*: Map to a specific echocardiographic calculation-method concept only when the source (typically a structured echo report) names that method; otherwise use the general 2D-echo or Doppler concept, or the generic cardiac output.\n- *Cardiac output vs. cardiac index*: This set is cardiac output (L/min). If the source value is normalised to body surface area (L/min/m², \"cardiac index\"), it is a different parameter and does not map here.\n- *Common source labels*: \"CO\", \"DC\" (débit cardiaque), \"Cardiac output\", \"Thermodilution CO\", \"CCO\" (continuous CO) → Cardiac output (4221102 / 82799009, SNOMED) or the matching method concept.\n- *Units*: Cardiac output is reported in L/min.\n\n## References\n\n[1] Vincent JL. Understanding cardiac output. Crit Care. 2008;12(4):174. Available: <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2575587/\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2575587/</a>"
      },
